comments.body: Little Mouse asked me to make a random selection, picking 4 users from each list.I'll use this draw methodology (slightly adjusted), with the hash from block 743650 (10 blocks in the future) as random input. I'll add the List number and numbers 1-4 to each hash to instantly get 20 random outputs.I'll use this, once the hash is known:Code:hash=00000000000000000xxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxfor List in 1 2 3 4 5; do Participants=`cat $List | wc -l`; for Winner in 1 2 3 4; do echo -n "List $List, Winner $Winner (out of $Participants): "; expr $(echo $hash$List$Winner | md5sum | tr -dc '0-9' | cut -c 1-8) % $Participants; done; echo; doneIf there's a duplicate, I'll manually increase the nonce to 5 or more until I have 4 unique numbers for each List.If there's a duplicate because there are
